<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,796,1144]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,941,868,893]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Recorded damage in the orchards of other parts of the world:</emphasis>
An occasional pest on citrus in 
<collectingCountry box="[1304,1432,868,893]" name="Serbia" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Yugoslavia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,203,903,928]" name="Italy" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Italy</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[256,323,903,928]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Spain</collectingCountry>
. A potentional pest in olive orchards in 
<collectingCountry box="[768,850,903,928]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. A vector of ' 
<emphasis box="[999,1032,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Ca</emphasis>
. Phytoplasma prunorum' (European stone fruit yellow phytoplasma), a potential career of almond witchesâ€™ broom phytoplasma (AlmWB) and tested positive to apricot chlorotic leaf roll (
<collectionCode box="[573,651,976,1000]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">ACLR</collectionCode>
) and phytoplasma in 
<collectingCountry box="[895,993,975,1000]" name="Lebanon" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1008,1166,975,1000]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491" refId="ref21713" refString="Reuther, W. (1989) The Citrus Industry: Crop Protection, Postharvest Technology, and Early History of Citrus Research in California. UCANR Publications, California, 374 pp." type="book">Reuther 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="16" pageNumber="491" refId="ref18269" refString="Bozbuga, R. &amp; Elekcioglu, Z. (2008) Pests and Natural Enemies Determined in Olive Orchards in Turkey. Turk Bilimsel Derlemeler Dergisi, 1 (1), 87 - 97." type="journal article">Bozbuga &amp; Elekcioglu 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[229,463,1012,1037]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491" refId="ref18421" refString="Dakhil, H. A., Abou-Fakhr, H. E., El-Mohtar, C. &amp; Abou-Jawdah, Y. (2011) Survey of leafhopper species in almond orchards infected with almond witches' - broom phytoplasma in Lebanon. Journal of Insect Science, 11 (Article 60), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1673 / 031.011.6001" type="journal article">
